g.aria-label: Import: Colorado River to Southern California

Atmospheric Water Generation would require between 300-650 kWh/m3making it by far the most energyintensive option. Surface and ground freshwater figures are reported byPan et al.The main source of varianceis the distance and elevation change that water needs to be transported, though the numbers include energyfor supply, treatment, and transport of water. Figures on Colorado River to Southern California imports,brackish desalination, and reclaimed water are given byWaterReuse. Energy intensity of desalination isreported byIRENA. The water treatment numbers are from Reekie, as reported by Gandiglio et al.Pan, S., Snyder, S., Packman, A., Lin, Y., Chiang, P.
